               (vdW) bilayers. Here, the study reports the twist-controlled
               ferroelectricity in tungsten diselenide (WSe2) bilayers. The
               findings show noticeable room temperature ferroelectricity that
               decreases with twist angle within the range 0° < θ < 3°, and
