               nonlinear crystals promise efficient photon-pair generation and
               on-chip monolithic integration with nanophotonic circuitry.
               However, it remains challenging to generate maximally entangled
               Bell states of photon pairs with high purity, generation rate,
               and fidelity required for practical applications. Here, we
               realize a polarization-entangled photon-pair source based on
               spontaneous parametric down conversion in an ultrathin
               rhombohedral tungsten disulfide (3R-WS2) crystal. This vdW
